ROCKY MOUNTAIN SPOTTED FEVER - MEXICO: (COAHUILA)
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 7 May 2014
Source: Milenio [in Spanish, machine transl., edited]
http://www.milenio.com/region/rickettsia-muertes-Ramos_Arizpe-Secretaria_de_Salud-Coahuila-prevencion_0_294571070.html


The University Hospital of Saltillo [Coahuila State] confirmed that a 59-year-old man, an inhabitant of the Cologne Armillita Ramos Arizpe, passed away this week from a rickettsial infection caused by a tick bite.

The Secretary of Health in Coahuila, Lauro Cortez Hernandez, noted that the clinic's notification was received and the case had already been confirmed by the National Institute of Diagnosis and Epidemiological Reference (INDRE), which to date has counted a total of 3 deaths from this cause. He said that the other deaths have been from Saltillo and General Cepeda [Coahuila State], confirming 5 cases so far in 2014 with the remaining 2 detected in San Pedro de las Colonias [Coahuila State].

[Byline: Raul Coronado Garces]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
